Layer-by-Layer Lineage

Layer 1 — Source Tables

Raw data loaded into the dbo schema. No transformations applied at this layer. Single flat table containing all bookings across all years.


Table	Key Column(s)	Notes
bookings	(no surrogate key)	119,390 rows. Composite natural key implied by hotel + arrival_date + customer attributes. All booking years combined in one table. Children column has NULL values. Country has NULL values. is_canceled and is_repeated_guest stored as INT (0/1), not boolean. Mixed formats in arrival date components (split across three columns). reservation_status and reservation_status_date present in raw but excluded from mart.

Key source columns:


Source Column	Type	Notes
hotel	varchar	'City Hotel' or 'Resort Hotel'
is_canceled	int	0/1 — not natively BIT
